figgy.title: Ensure that mudd [at] [domain] can upload Files and Folders using Google Drive
Figgy needs to be verified by Google

comments.body: This is currently blocking https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/issues/4525 from being advanced.

A YouTube video demonstrating the usage of Google Drive integration with Figgy, along with a description of the behavior of the application (in relation to Google Drive) was required in order to ensure that Figgy is verified by Google. This has been submitted for review, and the Trust and Safety team from Google should be expected to provide a response in, at most, 5 days.
I have just been notified that this is blocked due to `figgy.princeton.edu` domain not being verified with the Google Search Console service.
Empty TIFFs have been replaced on this item

requests.title: Initial work on updating alma test ids
ReCAP Flag Should be calculated using the remote storage flag

comments.body:
In order for SCSB to work with PUL owned items that are shelved in a remote_storage location when the request is placed it needs to:

1. Place a SCSB Physical Item Request for the item in question
2. If that is successful, place an Alma hold request for the same item. These requests should be identical to the hold requests that will be placed in Alma when this ticket is complete: https://github.com/pulibrary/requests/issues/933. 

Materials owned by SCSB partners will still only need a single SCSB Physical item request placed.

requests.title: What happens when Alma has a barcode but it is not real

comments.body:
1. On Order Records - These items *should* fall under the "Acquisition" process type and can be treated as on order requests
2. In Process Items (do these already have barcodes?) - Yes they do. These are items that are here and will be found under the label "Acquisition technical services", they can be treated as in process requests. 

These other non-barcoded items should still behave as they do now. 
1. Circulating Shelved holdings that aren't barcoded (send email to circ staff of non-standard request)
2. Partially barcoded multi-volume sets (send email to circ staff regarding non-standard request)
3. Special Collections holdings that aren't barcoded (send user directly to Aeon).
